OL,3,C'Like a family break up' says former
OL,4,CPontins worker 'devastated' at closure
OL,6,Fand staff are still "shocked and
OL,7,Fdevastated" at the way it was handled.
OL,9,FKevin O'Neill from Gwaenysgor was
OL,10,Flooking forward to his sixteenth year
OL,11,Fwith the company and says it's been
OL,12,Flike a "family break-up" for everyone
OL,13,Fwho worked there.
OL,15,FHe found out he was losing his job
OL,16,Ffrom a friend who used to work at the
OL,17,Fholiday park. He said: "There was no
OL,18,Fformal letter or anything. Nobody got
OL,19,Fanything. No word we were shutting
OL,20,Fdown.
