OL,3,C'Like a family break up' says former
OL,4,CPontins worker 'devastated' at closure
OL,6,F"There was one staff member who was
OL,7,Fvery, very upset because he'd just got
OL,8,Fa house, he just bought a new house
OL,9,Fand he was really struggling because
OL,10,Fthere was no money coming in, you
OL,11,Fknow, he had, he had kids and
OL,12,Feverything.
OL,14,F"He was getting really upset."
OL,16,FIt's had a big impact on people's
OL,17,Fhealth and wellbeing too according to
OL,18,FMr O'Neill. He says it's become a
OL,19,F"psychological thing" because "it's
OL,20,Fclose friends and members of your
OL,21,Fcommunity".
