OL,6,FHe added: "All of a sudden everybody's
OL,7,Fjust been dispersed. That bond that
OL,8,Fthey had, they've lost it.J"They feel
OL,9,Freally, really upset or upset, just
OL,10,Fdemoralized by, by the whole thing,
OL,11,Fyou know, the way it was treated."
OL,13,FMr O'Neill loved his job saying "the
OL,14,Fmoney was great" and "it was no
OL,15,Fhardship" being there.
OL,17,FHe continued: "I knew what job I was
OL,18,Fdoing and I enjoyed it. And the people
OL,19,Fthat were there were all great people
OL,20,Fand we used to see the same faces
OL,21,Fevery year.
