OL,3,C'Like a family break up' says former
OL,4,CPontins worker 'devastated' at closure
OL,6,F"We can't make any decisions until
OL,7,Fwe've had discussions with the owners
OL,8,FBritannia. And as I say, that's proved
OL,9,Fproblematic. It's a big site. Tourism
OL,10,Fis important to Prestatyn, to the
OL,11,Ftown, to the region. So the thoughts
OL,12,Fare, we'd like this to very much
OL,13,Fremain within tourism.J"We have had
OL,14,Fcontact with them. They arranged the
OL,15,Fmeeting and then quite suddenly
OL,16,Frearranged it. We're still awaiting a
OL,17,Fdate.J"It's important for a number of
OL,18,Freasons, primarily employment, jobs.
OL,19,FIt employed a lot of people here and
OL,20,Fstarting it's a large site as well,
OL,21,Fwhich cannot be kept empty for long.
OL,22,FIt's an important part of the history
OL,23,Fand culture of Prestatyn as well."
